Download Manager README
-----------------------------------------------------

To run this script:

python3 dm.py --arg1 --arg2

Use --help to see all available arguments

i.e. py3 dm.py --help

-----------------------------------------------------

This package requires:
* Python 3.4+
* Python Requests package

To enable extraction of compressed rar archives:
* Python rarfiles package

-----------------------------------------------------

Use pip to install Python third-party package:

* python3 -m pip install requests
* python3 -m pip install rarfile

To install this on Synology NAS the pip package must be installed first:

* Download get-pip.py to NAS downloads folder (google python pip for more info)
* SSH into DiskStation as root user: ssh root@$DISKSTATION
* Change directory to get-pip.py directory (e.g. cd /volume1/downloads/)
* Execute get-pip script: python3 get-pip.py
* Proceed with requests/rarfile install as before (e.g. python3 -m pip install requests)

-----------------------------------------------------

Note that for rar file extraction to function the unrar command line process must be installed.

This is available by default on Synology NAS OS but needs to be installed on Mac OS X.

To install on Mac OS X:
* Download package from RARlabs
* Extract package and navigate to newly created directory on the command line
* Install: sudo install -c -o $USER unrar /usr/local/bin
* Check install by typing unrar on the command line
